rComments: Prof Mathien delivered very interesting lectures and course assignments were fun to write. Fair marking from the TA's as well.

Amazing prof! He explains everything very clearly and takes the time to answer questions and explain things you don't understand. He doesn't post lecture notes and you'll need to primarily depend on your textbook for essays as well. You reap what you sow, work hard, and you'll do well.
Great course, very interesting, no essays. You can do great if you attend classes and listen carefully. I gathered most from classes not the book. Recommend the course strongly.

Mathien is hard to listen to.  He talks with his eyes closed, which makes you feel like you're going to fall asleep (since it seems like he is!).  The required texts are bizarre and really "out there" even for philosophy.  They're hard to understand, so the assignments are hard to do.  Good luck...you'll need it.

Prof. Mathien really knows his stuff. He is hard to listen to for 3 hours straight but he manages to crack a joke from time to time and attempts to get the class involved which makes it a little easier. His assignments are fair, and he is pretty easy going when it comes to marking. Overall, not bad.

He's the best. If you need any help, he's really easy to get a response from. He answers emails promptly and understands that students have obligations outside of school, and he accomodates that. Probably the best professor I've ever had.

Prof. Mathien knows his material well, however he is very tedious to listen to. It was a chore to go to lecture and listen to him speak, especially for two hours. He also has a habit of going over time, which is annoying because most people want to get out of his class. His  essays are fair and so is his marking. Poor/average professor overall.
